          "content": "## Project Analysis: Handi Cat Wallet Tracker\n\n### Overview\nA production-ready Telegram bot that tracks Solana wallet transactions in real-time, specifically monitoring DEX swaps on Raydium, Jupiter, Pump.fun, and PumpSwap. Built with TypeScript and designed for scalability.\n\n---\n\n### Architecture\n\n**Core Components:**\n\n1. **Telegram Bot Interface** (`src/bot/`)\n   - Commands: `/start`, `/add`, `/delete`, `/upgrade`, `/ban_wallet` (admin), `/help_notify`, `/help_group`\n   - Callback query handlers for interactive menus\n   - Group chat support\n\n2. **Wallet Tracking System** (`src/lib/track-wallets.ts`)\n   - Real-time transaction monitoring via Helius WebSocket (onLogs)\n   - Multi-RPC support for load distribution\n   - Automatic wallet pool management\n\n3. **Transaction Parser** (`src/parsers/transaction-parser.ts`)\n   - Detects swap types (Raydium, Jupiter, Pump.fun, PumpSwap)\n   - Extracts token amounts, prices, market caps\n   - Calculates supply percentages\n\n4. **Market Data** (`src/markets/`)\n   - Token price fetching (SOL denomination)\n   - Pump.fun bonding curve calculations\n   - Market cap calculations\n\n5. **Database Layer** (Prisma + PostgreSQL)\n   - User management with subscription tiers (FREE, HOBBY, PRO, WHALE)\n   - Wallet tracking with status management\n   - Promotion system\n   - Group chat associations\n\n---\n\n### Key Features\n\n**Subscription Model:**\n- FREE: Limited wallets\n- HOBBY/PRO/WHALE: Increased wallet limits\n- Monthly billing with renewal reminders (cron jobs)\n- Stackable promotions (e.g., upgrade to 50 wallets)\n\n**Wallet Management:**\n- Status tracking: ACTIVE, USER_PAUSED, SPAM_PAUSED, BANNED\n- Per-user wallet naming\n- Spam detection and auto-pause\n- Admin ban system\n\n**Transaction Detection:**\n- Program ID matching for DEX identification\n- SOL transfer tracking\n- Token metadata extraction\n- Supply percentage calculations\n- Links to trading bots (Photon, GMGN, Dex Screener)\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- Webhook support (production) or polling (development)\n- Rate limiting\n- Cron jobs for subscriptions and SOL price updates\n- Database backup scripts\n\n---\n\n### Technical Stack\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@solana/web3.js` - Blockchain interaction\n- `@raydium-io/raydium-sdk` - Raydium DEX parsing\n- `node-telegram-bot-api` - Bot framework\n- `@prisma/client` - ORM\n- `axios` - API calls (GMGN, Helius)\n- `node-cron` - Scheduled tasks\n- `express` - Webhook server\n\n**Development:**\n- TypeScript with strict typing\n- Prettier for formatting\n- Custom scripts for DB operations\n\n---\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. User adds wallet via `/add` command\n2. `TrackWallets` subscribes to wallet via Helius WebSocket\n3. On transaction, `TransactionParser` analyzes logs\n4. Market data fetched for token pricing\n5. Formatted message sent to user's Telegram\n6. Transaction links and bot shortcuts included\n\n---\n\n### Scalability Considerations\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Multi-RPC support prevents rate limiting\n- Wallet pool system for efficient monitoring\n- Subscription tiers control resource usage\n- Spam detection prevents abuse\n\n**Potential Bottlenecks:**\n- Single Helius WebSocket connection\n- Synchronous transaction parsing\n- Database queries per transaction\n\n---\n\n### Configuration\n\n**Environment Variables:**\n- `HELIUS_API_KEY` - WebSocket connection\n- `RPC_ENDPOINTS` - Comma-separated RPC URLs\n- `BOT_TOKEN` - Telegram bot token\n- `DATABASE_URL` - PostgreSQL connection\n- `ENVIRONMENT` - `development` (polling) or `production` (webhook)\n- `APP_URL` - Public HTTPS URL for webhooks\n\n---\n\n### Scripts\n\n- `pnpm start` - Build and run\n- `pnpm db:migrate` - Run migrations\n- `pnpm db:backup` - Backup database\n- `pnpm wallets:cleanup` - Clean up inactive wallets\n- `pnpm send:alert` - Send user alerts\n\n---\n\n### Code Quality\n\n**Positives:**\n- Well-organized directory structure\n- Type safety throughout\n- Separation of concerns (parsers, providers, repositories)\n- Constants for program IDs and pricing\n\n**Areas for Improvement:**\n- No test coverage (`test` script exits with error)\n- Large class files (TransactionParser: 466 lines)\n- Limited error handling visibility\n- No logging framework (uses console.log)\n\n---\n\n### Security Notes\n\n- Private keys stored in database (user personal wallets)\n- Admin commands protected by `ADMIN_CHAT_ID`\n- Banned wallet system prevents malicious tracking\n- Rate limiting implemented\n\n---\n\nThis is a well-structured production application with clear monetization strategy and solid Solana integration. The codebase is maintainable and shows good understanding of both blockchain and bot development patterns."
